  "prompt": "What is the meaning of the Tamil word \"ttha\"? Why is this word mostly used only in Chennai?",
  "response": "The Tamil word \"ttha\" (or sometimes written as \"dhadha\") primarily serves as an informal addressing term. It is a colloquial slang often used in Chennai to address someone in a familiar or playful manner, similar to saying \"dude\" or \"bro.\" This usage reflects the casual and friendly conversational style typical of the region. The popularity of \"ttha\" in Chennai can be attributed to the city's distinctive linguistic culture and its nuanced differences from other parts of Tamil Nadu.",
